# Behavioral vs Structural Modeling in Verilog

## Overview

| Aspect | Behavioral Modeling | Structural Modeling |
|--------|---------------------|---------------------|
| **Focus** | What the circuit does | How the circuit is built |
| **Abstraction** | High-level (algorithmic) | Low-level (component instantiation) |
| **Simulation Speed** | Faster (less detail) | Slower (more detail) |
| **Use Case** | Top-level design, algorithms | Detailed implementation, optimization |
| **Synthesis** | May need optimization | Direct mapping to gates |

